Step 1: Identify the relevant data.
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from the cash flow statement) is –6,316,405.44.
• Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) is the sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable = 3,500,000.00 + 819,436.82 = 4,319,436.82.

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• The formula is:
  Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)
• Substitute the numbers:
  = (–6,316,405.44) / (4,319,436.82)
  ≈ –1.46

Thus, the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio is approximately –1.46.
